WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.506 --> 00:00:07.508
<i>Previously on</i>
Criminal Minds: Evolution...

2
00:00:07.745 --> 00:00:10.487
Moving now will give Henry
some time to make some memories

3
00:00:10.511 --> 00:00:12.904
at the new place
before he moves away

4
00:00:13.078 --> 00:00:15.316
to some dorm somewhere.

5
00:00:15.363 --> 00:00:16.886
He'll probably
stay on the east coast?

6
00:00:16.973 --> 00:00:18.714
California's always been
on his list.

7
00:00:18.801 --> 00:00:21.934
- How long are you out for?
- Contractor said two.

8
00:00:22.065 --> 00:00:23.545
maybe three weeks.

9
00:00:23.719 --> 00:00:24.894
- Thank you for this.
- Mm.

10
00:00:24.981 --> 00:00:25.938
Why conduct these interviews?

11
00:00:26.113 --> 00:00:28.202
So we can learn how Lee Duval

12
00:00:28.332 --> 00:00:30.291
became Elias Voit
became Sicarius.

13
00:00:30.421 --> 00:00:33.250
You think. if I walk you
through everything.

14
00:00:33.337 --> 00:00:35.078
you'll be able
to stop someone else?

15
00:00:35.165 --> 00:00:37.298
Welcome to The Sicarius Files.

16
00:00:37.428 --> 00:00:38.473
May I call you Elias?

17
00:00:39.735 --> 00:00:41.041
Oh!

18
00:00:41.128 --> 00:00:42.651
It's sad how pathetic I am.

19
00:00:42.781 --> 00:00:44.087
But you know
what's even more pathetic?

20
00:00:44.218 --> 00:00:45.915
Someone who makes
a show about it.

21
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:48.048
And anyone who listens to it.

22
00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:56.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

23
00:01:56.638 --> 00:01:58.422
What do you want?

24
00:02:00.511 --> 00:02:01.904
There's cash in the bedroom
upstairs. all right?

25
00:02:02.034 --> 00:02:03.210
Just take it.

26
00:02:05.473 --> 00:02:07.301
Take anything you want.

27
00:02:07.431 --> 00:02:09.477
Please. just leave us alone.

28
00:02:09.607 --> 00:02:12.219
You believe money will free you?

29
00:02:12.349 --> 00:02:14.177
Yeah.
That's what you want. right?

30
00:02:15.613 --> 00:02:16.440
No.

31
00:02:17.789 --> 00:02:19.226
Heresy.

32
00:02:22.185 --> 00:02:24.100
Heresy is the reason I'm here.

33
00:02:24.274 --> 00:02:26.450
- Heresy?
- What are you talking about?

34
00:02:26.581 --> 00:02:27.843
Confess.

35
00:02:29.279 --> 00:02:30.367
I don't understand
what you're talking about.

36
00:02:30.454 --> 00:02:32.935
For God's sake. just tell him.

37
00:02:33.065 --> 00:02:34.197
Tell him what? I don't know!

38
00:02:34.328 --> 00:02:35.938
I don't know! Whatever you did.

39
00:02:37.244 --> 00:02:39.768
Tell me!

40
00:02:39.898 --> 00:02:41.378
- Christ!
- No! No!

41
00:02:41.509 --> 00:02:43.598
- Please...
- Tell me!

42
00:02:43.685 --> 00:02:45.730
Please. Please.

43
00:02:45.904 --> 00:02:47.079
We have a son.

44
00:02:47.254 --> 00:02:49.517
Okay. all right.

45
00:02:49.647 --> 00:02:51.606
I confess.

46
00:02:51.736 --> 00:02:53.564
What?

47
00:02:53.695 --> 00:02:54.913
I confess.

48
00:02:55.043 --> 00:02:57.089
The truth is...

49
00:02:58.134 --> 00:02:59.918
It was me. all right?
I was the one.

50
00:03:00.092 --> 00:03:01.833
I ordered the layoffs
at the company last year. okay?

51
00:03:01.964 --> 00:03:03.922
Oh. God. Charles.

52
00:03:04.053 --> 00:03:06.490
I know. I know. I know.

53
00:03:06.621 --> 00:03:08.144
We didn't need to do it.
but we did. all right?

54
00:03:08.318 --> 00:03:10.190
And if you were
one of those people. I...

55
00:03:10.277 --> 00:03:11.495
I'm sorry.

56
00:03:12.670 --> 00:03:14.281
All right? I-It was a mistake.

57
00:03:14.455 --> 00:03:15.891
We shouldn't have done it.

58
00:03:16.065 --> 00:03:18.807
He can... he can
make this right.

59
00:03:18.937 --> 00:03:20.765
- You can do that. can't you?
- Uh.

60
00:03:20.896 --> 00:03:22.071
yes. of course. of course I can.

61
00:03:22.158 --> 00:03:23.986
See? He can fix this for you.

62
00:03:24.116 --> 00:03:27.424
Uh. this can be all over.
and you can let us go.

63
00:03:27.555 --> 00:03:29.774
Yeah. I-I sw...
I-I swear to God.

64
00:03:29.861 --> 00:03:31.298
Yeah. I...

65
00:03:31.428 --> 00:03:32.690
Yeah. I swear.

66
00:03:32.777 --> 00:03:35.389
- Just go. No!
- I sw... - Yes!

67
00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:37.478
Oh. my God!

68
00:03:47.488 --> 00:03:50.012
"One's work
may be finished someday.

69
00:03:50.186 --> 00:03:51.883
but one's education? Never."

70
00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:54.103
Alexandre Dumas.

71
00:03:56.975 --> 00:03:59.108
All of these pages.

72
00:03:59.195 --> 00:04:00.109
and they're not photoshopped?

73
00:04:00.283 --> 00:04:03.243
No. In fact.
forensics confirmed

74
00:04:03.417 --> 00:04:05.027
that ink was pressed to paper
with the typebars

75
00:04:05.157 --> 00:04:07.247
of an analog typewriter.

76
00:04:07.334 --> 00:04:08.465
Jesus.

77
00:04:08.552 --> 00:04:11.338
I mean. the time and effort.

78
00:04:11.512 --> 00:04:13.557
Someone really
did not appreciate

79
00:04:13.688 --> 00:04:15.385
Voit calling them pathetic
on Garrity's podcast.

80
00:04:15.516 --> 00:04:17.909
How seriously
should we take this?

81
00:04:17.995 --> 00:04:19.998
Voit thinks "very seriously."

82
00:04:20.129 --> 00:04:21.783
He thinks it's a threat?

83
00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:23.654
He thinks it's intended
to get his undivided attention.

84
00:04:23.785 --> 00:04:26.744
Like some crazy.
disillusioned fan?

85
00:04:26.875 --> 00:04:29.138
Who now has something to prove.

86
00:04:29.225 --> 00:04:31.183
So. we could be
looking at Voit's

87
00:04:31.314 --> 00:04:34.099
very own Mark David Chapman.

88
00:04:34.230 --> 00:04:35.797
I assume no prints
were recovered?

89
00:04:35.971 --> 00:04:38.713
Or DNA.
But based on the postmark.

90
00:04:38.843 --> 00:04:40.236
we believe it was
deposited in a drop box

91
00:04:40.367 --> 00:04:42.194
somewhere
in Kensington. Pennsylvania.

92
00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:43.718
It's a neighborhood
in Northeast Philly.

93
00:04:43.848 --> 00:04:45.502
Okay. well. that narrows
it down. doesn't it?

94
00:04:45.589 --> 00:04:46.808
It does.

95
00:04:46.938 --> 00:04:48.418
Have you followed up
with Voit yet?

96
00:04:48.592 --> 00:04:50.202
Um. I'm gonna head there now.

97
00:04:50.332 --> 00:04:52.379
- Keep me updated.
- Absolutely.

98
00:05:14.270 --> 00:05:16.011
Okay. so...

99
00:05:16.141 --> 00:05:19.406
pretty sure I am being ghosted
by my son.

100
00:05:20.972 --> 00:05:23.801
Oof. Three texts and no reply.

101
00:05:23.932 --> 00:05:26.413
That's... teenagers.

102
00:05:26.543 --> 00:05:29.198
Henry's gone MIA before.
but this?

103
00:05:29.372 --> 00:05:31.809
This is like
texting with a monk.

104
00:05:31.896 --> 00:05:33.463
Probably overwhelmed.

105
00:05:33.550 --> 00:05:36.379
You know. college applications
and everything. I...

106
00:05:36.510 --> 00:05:38.599
Maybe why
he wants to stay local.

107
00:05:38.686 --> 00:05:40.296
Local?

108
00:05:40.427 --> 00:05:41.471
Wait. what are you
talking about?

109
00:05:41.602 --> 00:05:44.082
I-I told him
he should talk to you.

110
00:05:44.213 --> 00:05:44.953
- I-I guess...
- This is the first

111
00:05:45.082 --> 00:05:46.171
I'm hearing about it.

112
00:05:46.302 --> 00:05:47.999
- What... what do you mean?
- Oh.

113
00:05:48.086 --> 00:05:49.871
I'm interrupting.
My doves. there is something

114
00:05:50.045 --> 00:05:51.655
out in Colorado that
desperately needs our attention.

115
00:05:51.786 --> 00:05:52.917
Sorry. Let's go.

116
00:05:53.004 --> 00:05:54.789
Okay.

117
00:05:54.963 --> 00:05:56.443
Uh...

118
00:05:59.576 --> 00:06:00.882
My people.

119
00:06:01.012 --> 00:06:02.753
the crossword clue
of the day is "heresy."

120
00:06:02.884 --> 00:06:05.016
as in "sacrilege."
"blasphemy." "heathenism."

121
00:06:05.147 --> 00:06:07.889
I bring this up because we have
an unsub in Colorado Springs

122
00:06:08.019 --> 00:06:10.239
who has killed
at least two women

123
00:06:10.326 --> 00:06:12.633
by beating them to death with...
dear Goddess... a sledgehammer.

124
00:06:12.763 --> 00:06:15.505
but not before accusing
the latest victim. Mary Tolson.

125
00:06:15.679 --> 00:06:17.246
of... you guessed it... heresy.

126
00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:19.727
Leaving a living witness
is a pretty bold statement.

127
00:06:19.901 --> 00:06:21.816
And risky. considering

128
00:06:21.903 --> 00:06:23.905
he's not concealing his face.

129
00:06:24.035 --> 00:06:26.473
Penelope. have either
surviving spouses

130
00:06:26.603 --> 00:06:27.909
met with a sketch artist?

131
00:06:28.039 --> 00:06:29.563
Yeah. but the descriptions
were so vague

132
00:06:29.737 --> 00:06:31.260
that local PD
don't think they're any help.

133
00:06:31.347 --> 00:06:33.262
He must present as very average.
hard to identify.

134
00:06:33.436 --> 00:06:34.959
especially since he's also

135
00:06:35.133 --> 00:06:37.092
getting in and out
of the victims' homes unseen.

136
00:06:37.222 --> 00:06:40.051
And that speaks to a high level
of organization and planning.

137
00:06:40.182 --> 00:06:42.402
Coupled with an explosive rage.

138
00:06:42.576 --> 00:06:44.447
I-I mean.
to-to use a sledgehammer

139
00:06:44.534 --> 00:06:46.101
to essentially destroy a family

140
00:06:46.231 --> 00:06:49.321
for some kind of...
what. perceived sin?

141
00:06:49.452 --> 00:06:52.107
Time-out. All men. please
immediately go to therapy.

142
00:06:52.281 --> 00:06:53.891
Thank you. Time back in.

143
00:06:54.022 --> 00:06:55.850
But the fact remains

144
00:06:56.024 --> 00:06:57.939
that he is-is not

145
00:06:58.113 --> 00:07:00.985
committing physical violence
against the whole family.

146
00:07:01.116 --> 00:07:02.422
No. he's inflicting

147
00:07:02.596 --> 00:07:05.294
emotional violence
to the surviving family.

148
00:07:05.381 --> 00:07:08.297
Especially to the husbands.

149
00:07:08.384 --> 00:07:10.430
since it appears the unsub
broke into the homes

150
00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:13.781
after the teenage children
left for school.

151
00:07:13.955 --> 00:07:15.347
So. sparing those kids
from actually

152
00:07:15.478 --> 00:07:16.697
having to witness the violence

153
00:07:16.827 --> 00:07:18.655
could speak to the unsub's
own history of trauma.

154
00:07:18.786 --> 00:07:21.484
And maybe the heresy
this unsub perceives

155
00:07:21.571 --> 00:07:23.268
has something to do
with a fucked-up way

156
00:07:23.399 --> 00:07:24.748
of protecting them.

157
00:07:24.879 --> 00:07:26.576
All right. Dave. Tyler.

158
00:07:26.707 --> 00:07:28.752
we are headed
to Colorado Springs.

159
00:07:28.926 --> 00:07:30.928
Luke. JJ. I need you two
to stay behind and help Tara

160
00:07:31.059 --> 00:07:31.886
with Voit.

161
00:07:32.016 --> 00:07:33.322
Looks like he has sparked

162
00:07:33.409 --> 00:07:35.498
a fire that we are going
to have to put out.

163
00:07:38.806 --> 00:07:40.198
Laundry crew from C block.

164
00:07:40.329 --> 00:07:41.808
authorized to work area three...

165
00:07:43.724 --> 00:07:45.203
Laundry crew from C block

166
00:07:45.334 --> 00:07:46.988
authorized to work area three.

167
00:07:47.118 --> 00:07:49.381
You struck quite a nerve
out there.

168
00:07:49.556 --> 00:07:51.253
Whoever this was
couldn't help himself.

169
00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:52.994
He had to respond.

170
00:07:53.124 --> 00:07:55.387
With... geometry?

171
00:07:55.518 --> 00:07:56.780
This all means something to him.

172
00:07:56.911 --> 00:07:59.000
I bet he typed up
dozens and dozens of these

173
00:07:59.130 --> 00:08:00.392
that weren't "good enough"
to send.

174
00:08:00.523 --> 00:08:03.744
Okay. So you're saying
he's patient.

175
00:08:03.874 --> 00:08:05.876
I'm saying he's precise.

176
00:08:05.963 --> 00:08:07.704
He's like you.

177
00:08:09.053 --> 00:08:10.141
The old you.

178
00:08:10.228 --> 00:08:11.621
He aspires to be.

179
00:08:11.752 --> 00:08:13.362
All right. so you don't think
he's committed

180
00:08:13.493 --> 00:08:14.798
an act of violence yet?

181
00:08:14.929 --> 00:08:16.147
I don't.

182
00:08:16.278 --> 00:08:17.409
This sort of focus...
it's transference.

183
00:08:17.540 --> 00:08:18.715
He's still evolving.

184
00:08:18.846 --> 00:08:22.023
All right. But this kind
of transference...

185
00:08:22.153 --> 00:08:23.764
not to mention
a highly developed

186
00:08:23.894 --> 00:08:25.679
obsessive-compulsive disorder...

187
00:08:25.809 --> 00:08:27.681
- may be innocuous on their own...
- Yeah.

188
00:08:27.811 --> 00:08:29.683
but mix the two together. it
can take you into the darkness.

189
00:08:29.857 --> 00:08:32.163
especially when you've suffered
an injury to your ego.

190
00:08:32.294 --> 00:08:33.121
Yeah.

191
00:08:33.207 --> 00:08:34.775
Thanks to you.

192
00:08:39.388 --> 00:08:43.131
I was a little pissed off
when I went at Garrity. okay?

193
00:08:43.260 --> 00:08:45.307
And. yes. I maybe...
I maybe could've chosen

194
00:08:45.437 --> 00:08:48.005
my words a little more wisely.
but I...

195
00:08:48.136 --> 00:08:49.746
And you should have.

196
00:08:49.877 --> 00:08:51.400
You said it yourself:

197
00:08:51.574 --> 00:08:53.707
your celebrity
carries influence.

198
00:08:53.837 --> 00:08:56.927
This guy is just looking
for a reason to get started.

199
00:08:57.058 --> 00:08:59.843
This isn't gonna be
the last time he reaches out.

200
00:08:59.974 --> 00:09:00.844
Yeah.

201
00:09:00.975 --> 00:09:02.454
Well...

202
00:09:02.629 --> 00:09:04.761
that's what we're counting on.

203
00:09:07.590 --> 00:09:09.592
He zip-tied Mary Tolson.

204
00:09:09.679 --> 00:09:11.289
dragged her.

205
00:09:11.420 --> 00:09:12.987
Same drag marks
from the legs of the chairs

206
00:09:13.117 --> 00:09:15.076
were at the house
of victim one. Zoe Faldo.

207
00:09:15.250 --> 00:09:17.121
He's making the victims
face their husbands

208
00:09:17.295 --> 00:09:18.427
before he kills them.

209
00:09:18.514 --> 00:09:20.385
Maybe he's shaming the wives?

210
00:09:20.516 --> 00:09:21.822
Maybe because
he has his own wife

211
00:09:21.952 --> 00:09:23.475
that he blames for the end
of their relationship?

212
00:09:23.650 --> 00:09:25.042
Could explain
the explosion of anger.

213
00:09:25.173 --> 00:09:26.653
It's possible.

214
00:09:26.783 --> 00:09:29.612
Lot of unsubs are triggered
by marriages ending.

215
00:09:30.657 --> 00:09:33.616
Why not take out that physical
violence on the entire family?

216
00:09:33.747 --> 00:09:35.662
Why switch
to a psychological torture?

217
00:09:35.792 --> 00:09:39.448
Particularly on the husbands
who are forced to sit and watch.

218
00:09:43.321 --> 00:09:46.673
Ooh. I see those wheels turning.

219
00:09:46.760 --> 00:09:49.719
Let's hear your theory.
Agent Green.

220
00:09:50.720 --> 00:09:52.722
Something feels off
about what happened

221
00:09:52.896 --> 00:09:54.158
between the two victims.

222
00:09:54.332 --> 00:09:56.117
The husband of victim one.
Gary Faldo.

223
00:09:56.204 --> 00:09:58.119
said the unsub knocked him out
before killing his wife.

224
00:09:58.293 --> 00:10:01.470
But he didn't mention the unsub
saying anything about heresy.

225
00:10:01.557 --> 00:10:04.516
And the first time
that word popped up was...

226
00:10:04.647 --> 00:10:05.953
right here. with the Tolsons.

227
00:10:06.083 --> 00:10:07.694
What if-what if Charles Tolson

228
00:10:07.824 --> 00:10:09.130
heard about what happened
with the Faldos...

229
00:10:09.304 --> 00:10:12.046
And he hired a guy to make it
look like the same crime.

230
00:10:12.176 --> 00:10:13.787
Copycat crime.

231
00:10:13.917 --> 00:10:15.527
And he gets to draft
off the media frenzy.

232
00:10:15.658 --> 00:10:17.399
I know it sounds elaborate.

233
00:10:17.529 --> 00:10:18.530
Sometimes the more elaborate.

234
00:10:18.705 --> 00:10:20.794
- the easier it is to mislead.
- Right.

235
00:10:20.924 --> 00:10:24.232
But the only problem
with your theory is...

236
00:10:24.362 --> 00:10:26.016
the blood on the zip ties.

237
00:10:26.147 --> 00:10:27.191
What blood?

238
00:10:27.322 --> 00:10:28.540
Go to the last page.

239
00:10:34.024 --> 00:10:35.504
Thoughts?

240
00:10:35.678 --> 00:10:36.810
Yeah.

241
00:10:36.940 --> 00:10:39.639
Charles Tolson
was trying to get free

242
00:10:39.769 --> 00:10:41.684
when the unsub
started killing his wife.

243
00:10:41.815 --> 00:10:43.904
So much so that he cut
through his own flesh.

244
00:10:45.427 --> 00:10:48.778
Not really the effort you'd make
if you hired the killer.

245
00:10:48.952 --> 00:10:50.475
Not so much.

246
00:10:50.606 --> 00:10:51.520
You knew that the whole time?

247
00:10:51.651 --> 00:10:52.826
What did I tell you?

248
00:10:52.956 --> 00:10:54.915
Reps.
You need more reps.

249
00:10:55.045 --> 00:10:58.222
You always have to run through
a few bad theories

250
00:10:58.396 --> 00:10:59.180
to get to the good ones.

251
00:10:59.310 --> 00:11:01.051
I guess.

252
00:11:01.182 --> 00:11:02.618
Now. you need to start living
in the crime scene more.

253
00:11:02.749 --> 00:11:04.011
Let's. uh... Here.

254
00:11:04.185 --> 00:11:05.621
Take a seat.

255
00:11:07.841 --> 00:11:11.366
Now. I'm the unsub
and I have a sledgehammer.

256
00:11:11.496 --> 00:11:12.541
You're accusing me of heresy.

257
00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:14.282
- What else?
- You're...

258
00:11:14.412 --> 00:11:15.239
demanding answers.

259
00:11:15.413 --> 00:11:16.763
You're interrogating me.

260
00:11:16.893 --> 00:11:19.113
Would I tie you up
