And based on our profile.
whoever wrote Voit

795
00:34:24.453 --> 00:34:27.108
suffers from an
obsessive-compulsive disorder.

796
00:34:27.239 --> 00:34:28.414
Right. and if Lance
was that guy.

797
00:34:28.543 --> 00:34:29.719
he would have lost his shit

798
00:34:29.850 --> 00:34:30.938
when that ink
went all over the place.

799
00:34:31.025 --> 00:34:33.853
Okay. so.
Lance took the photos...

800
00:34:34.027 --> 00:34:35.246
But there's no way
he mailed them.

801
00:34:35.377 --> 00:34:37.553
I mean. he didn't even know
they were stolen.

802
00:34:37.726 --> 00:34:41.034
So. Voit's fan is certainly
following in his footsteps.

803
00:34:41.166 --> 00:34:44.168
So he would have to have
the technological know-how

804
00:34:44.299 --> 00:34:46.214
- to access Lance's digital domain.
- Right.

805
00:34:46.388 --> 00:34:48.608
And I'm starting to think
that he deliberately

806
00:34:48.695 --> 00:34:51.567
offered up this Lance guy here
for our consideration.

807
00:34:51.654 --> 00:34:53.699
- Yeah. it does.
- I'll tell you something else.

808
00:34:53.830 --> 00:34:55.614
I am not feeling great about

809
00:34:55.745 --> 00:34:57.486
releasing Lance
back in to Laura's orbit.

810
00:34:57.660 --> 00:34:59.271
No. yeah.
I don't think a stern warning

811
00:34:59.358 --> 00:35:01.882
- is gonna keep that guy away.
- Yeah. me neither.

812
00:35:03.405 --> 00:35:04.711
But...

813
00:35:04.798 --> 00:35:07.061
maybe there is a way

814
00:35:07.192 --> 00:35:08.889
that we can drive the point home

815
00:35:09.019 --> 00:35:11.500
that he needs to keep
his distance from Laura.

816
00:35:11.587 --> 00:35:14.112
Okay. How?

817
00:35:14.938 --> 00:35:16.679
Little extra muscle?

818
00:35:19.813 --> 00:35:21.380
Who the fuck are you?

819
00:35:21.467 --> 00:35:24.209
I'm the guy
you need to listen to.

820
00:35:24.339 --> 00:35:26.646
You see that camera up there?

821
00:35:26.776 --> 00:35:28.996
I know.
You're watching me.

822
00:35:29.127 --> 00:35:30.737
You know why we're watching you?

823
00:35:30.867 --> 00:35:32.217
No.

824
00:35:32.304 --> 00:35:34.871
We're watching you
for your own protection.

825
00:35:35.045 --> 00:35:36.264
Protection?

826
00:35:36.438 --> 00:35:37.657
- What do you...
- We know you took

827
00:35:37.787 --> 00:35:39.354
those pictures of Laura.

828
00:35:39.528 --> 00:35:41.835
Okay? But the person
that we're looking for

829
00:35:41.922 --> 00:35:44.011
has been keeping eyes on you.

830
00:35:44.142 --> 00:35:45.621
We need to find that guy

831
00:35:45.708 --> 00:35:47.884
so that you're no longer
a person of interest.

832
00:35:48.015 --> 00:35:49.538
but we're running out of time.

833
00:35:49.712 --> 00:35:51.149
Because pretty soon.

834
00:35:51.279 --> 00:35:52.715
we're not going to be able
to watch over you.

835
00:35:52.889 --> 00:35:55.762
- Mm. That's fucking fine by me.
- No. it's not fine.

836
00:35:55.892 --> 00:35:58.504
You need someone
checking in on you.

837
00:35:58.591 --> 00:36:00.375
You're the type of guy.
you've picked a fight

838
00:36:00.506 --> 00:36:03.248
with almost everyone
in your life and lost.

839
00:36:03.378 --> 00:36:05.293
From employers
to your own mother.

840
00:36:10.733 --> 00:36:12.126
My mother loves me.

841
00:36:23.398 --> 00:36:25.661
Lance. when you came in here.
you volunteered your phone.

842
00:36:25.792 --> 00:36:28.098
That's how we found
the photos of Laura.

843
00:36:28.229 --> 00:36:31.276
But we also noticed that there
were a lot of outgoing calls

844
00:36:31.406 --> 00:36:32.494
to your mom.

845
00:36:32.668 --> 00:36:34.627
No return calls.

846
00:36:34.714 --> 00:36:36.542
Not even a text.

847
00:36:38.065 --> 00:36:39.501
She's...

848
00:36:40.807 --> 00:36:42.548
She says she's busy.

849
00:36:42.722 --> 00:36:45.246
I'm sure she is.
That's not my point.

850
00:36:45.377 --> 00:36:46.726
My point

851
00:36:46.900 --> 00:36:50.860
is that you need someone

852
00:36:50.991 --> 00:36:52.384
to check in on you.

853
00:36:52.471 --> 00:36:54.386
Without that. I mean.
you could go missing

854
00:36:54.560 --> 00:36:56.170
and no one would notice.

855
00:36:56.301 --> 00:36:58.172
Not for a long time.

856
00:36:58.346 --> 00:37:00.348
Maybe ever.

857
00:37:00.522 --> 00:37:03.569
If you bother Laura again.

858
00:37:03.743 --> 00:37:05.571
I won't like that.

859
00:37:06.659 --> 00:37:08.269
You hear me?

860
00:37:09.836 --> 00:37:12.230
Yeah. I hear you.

861
00:37:20.890 --> 00:37:23.197
Leave Laura alone.

862
00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:34.382
Muscle.

863
00:37:34.469 --> 00:37:36.558
So. if the victims' kids
don't know each other.

864
00:37:36.645 --> 00:37:38.865
how can the unsub be connected
to all three families?

865
00:37:38.995 --> 00:37:41.955
Garcia cross-referenced
their social groups.

866
00:37:42.042 --> 00:37:43.870
school and extracurricular.

867
00:37:44.000 --> 00:37:44.784
Nothing popped up.

868
00:37:44.958 --> 00:37:46.742
What about school staff?

869
00:37:46.829 --> 00:37:48.396
The guy blends
into the background.

870
00:37:48.483 --> 00:37:50.224
I mean. it's not like
the kids confide in him

871
00:37:50.398 --> 00:37:52.444
but more that he can eavesdrop

872
00:37:52.618 --> 00:37:54.315
on their conversations.

873
00:37:54.489 --> 00:37:56.186
Sure. If the kids knew their
parents were having problems.

874
00:37:56.274 --> 00:37:57.362
they'd talk
to friends at school.

875
00:37:57.449 --> 00:37:59.059
We know he's highly educated.

876
00:37:59.189 --> 00:38:01.191
so we would definitely qualify
to teach history

877
00:38:01.279 --> 00:38:03.324
- or English.
- But what teacher works

878
00:38:03.455 --> 00:38:04.847
at three different schools
in three different districts?

879
00:38:05.979 --> 00:38:07.285
A part-time one.

880
00:38:08.111 --> 00:38:09.809
A substitute.

881
00:38:12.377 --> 00:38:14.248
I hinge on your every need. sir.
How can I help?

882
00:38:14.379 --> 00:38:16.250
Penelope. cross-reference

883
00:38:16.381 --> 00:38:17.643
the schools
where our victims' kids

884
00:38:17.817 --> 00:38:19.732
were enrolled in.

885
00:38:19.906 --> 00:38:21.908
We're looking for the name
of a substitute teacher

886
00:38:22.082 --> 00:38:23.431
employed by all three.

887
00:38:23.605 --> 00:38:25.041
Focus on anyone

888
00:38:25.128 --> 00:38:26.652
with advanced
education credentials.

889
00:38:26.782 --> 00:38:29.785
Got it. Overqualified
temporary employee...

890
00:38:29.872 --> 00:38:31.918
Mm...

891
00:38:32.048 --> 00:38:33.136
Wait. Do I have it?

892
00:38:33.267 --> 00:38:36.096
I just might. Sean Fincher.

893
00:38:36.226 --> 00:38:37.402
He's a substitute teacher.

894
00:38:37.532 --> 00:38:38.751
he specializes
in advanced history.

895
00:38:38.881 --> 00:38:40.927
and I got pay stubs
from all three schools.

896
00:38:41.057 --> 00:38:43.364
Is there anything else
we need to know?

897
00:38:43.495 --> 00:38:45.018
Uh. I'm searching
court records right now.

898
00:38:45.192 --> 00:38:46.672
Oh. wow.

899
00:38:46.802 --> 00:38:49.196
When Sean was 15. his
fire-and-brimstone pastor pop

900
00:38:49.283 --> 00:38:51.720
beat his mom to death.
C.O.D.:

901
00:38:51.851 --> 00:38:53.592
blunt force trauma to the head.

902
00:38:53.722 --> 00:38:55.115
and the father is currently
spending life in prison.

903
00:38:55.245 --> 00:38:56.464
Does Sean have any other family?

904
00:38:56.595 --> 00:38:58.423
Uh...

905
00:38:59.467 --> 00:39:01.251
Well. he had a wife. Marta.

906
00:39:01.339 --> 00:39:02.688
She filed for divorce
four weeks ago

907
00:39:02.862 --> 00:39:05.691
and she moved herself
and their son Elijah

908
00:39:05.865 --> 00:39:07.388
to Tempe. Arizona.

909
00:39:07.475 --> 00:39:08.998
That's what triggered him.

910
00:39:09.129 --> 00:39:11.044
Garcia. what is the last class
Fincher taught?

911
00:39:11.131 --> 00:39:13.133
The parents
of one of those students

912
00:39:13.263 --> 00:39:14.439
has to be his next target.

913
00:39:14.569 --> 00:39:16.832
I-I... I'm searching
at warp speed.

914
00:39:36.374 --> 00:39:38.071
Are you ready to confess?

915
00:39:40.726 --> 00:39:44.382
Look. I don't know who you are.
but don't do this.

916
00:39:45.426 --> 00:39:46.732
Are you ready?

917
00:39:48.734 --> 00:39:50.518
This is a mistake.

918
00:39:50.649 --> 00:39:52.128
Please.

919
00:39:58.831 --> 00:40:00.528
Oh. my God.

920
00:40:03.096 --> 00:40:05.533
Confess your heresy.

921
00:40:08.101 --> 00:40:09.319
Heresy? Oh. God.

922
00:40:09.494 --> 00:40:11.887
Tell him. Brenton.
Just tell him.

923
00:40:12.018 --> 00:40:13.149
What?

924
00:40:13.280 --> 00:40:14.629
Tell him or I will.

925
00:40:15.543 --> 00:40:17.502
It's got to be why he's here.

926
00:40:17.589 --> 00:40:18.546
No.

927
00:40:18.677 --> 00:40:19.852
My husband cheated on me.

928
00:40:19.982 --> 00:40:21.157
Ugh. Jesus.

929
00:40:21.288 --> 00:40:22.985
That's what he has to confess.

930
00:40:23.159 --> 00:40:24.030
Goddamn it. Okay.

931
00:40:24.160 --> 00:40:25.466
All right. I-I confess.

932
00:40:25.597 --> 00:40:28.426
- Is that what you want?
- Shh!

933
00:40:29.339 --> 00:40:32.299
Judgment will be cast...

934
00:40:32.386 --> 00:40:34.693
No. no. wait.
I thought that...

935
00:40:34.780 --> 00:40:36.434
...and punishment rendered.

936
00:40:36.564 --> 00:40:38.174
- No. no. please.
- Fuck you.

937
00:40:39.349 --> 00:40:41.003
- Fuck you!
- You haven't heard my confession!

938
00:40:50.186 --> 00:40:51.753
Penelope. have you found
the student?

939
00:40:54.234 --> 00:40:56.279
Yes. Kima Woodrow.

940
00:40:57.846 --> 00:41:00.109
Her father Brenton has had
a lot of spendy dinners

941
00:41:00.240 --> 00:41:02.068
while her mom. Delores.
has been out of town.

942
00:41:02.198 --> 00:41:04.157
Okay. we'll have locals
pick Kima up from school.

943
00:41:04.244 --> 00:41:05.375
Send us the Woodrows'
home address.

944
00:41:05.506 --> 00:41:07.247
It's sent. Be careful.

945
00:41:12.165 --> 00:41:13.862
You want the truth?

946
00:41:15.081 --> 00:41:16.430
I cheated. too.

947
00:41:21.609 --> 00:41:23.219
Judgment will be...

948
00:41:23.350 --> 00:41:25.395
Just do what you got to do.
goddamn it!

949
00:41:25.526 --> 00:41:27.659
No. wait. wait.
She's lying. okay?

950
00:41:27.746 --> 00:41:30.792
- She's just trying to save me.
- Silence!

951
00:41:30.879 --> 00:41:33.534
I have only one question

952
00:41:33.665 --> 00:41:36.450
before I render judgment.

953
00:41:36.581 --> 00:41:39.671
Who committed the heresy first?

954
00:41:44.327 --> 00:41:48.027
Kima deserves so much better
than you both.

955
00:41:48.157 --> 00:41:49.811
Kima? What?

956
00:41:49.898 --> 00:41:52.118
You son of a bitch.
you know my daughter?

957
00:41:52.292 --> 00:41:53.815
How the fuck
do you know my daughter?

958
00:41:53.902 --> 00:41:55.948
How about our son?

959
00:41:56.078 --> 00:41:57.863
Do you even know
what happened to him?

960
00:42:02.781 --> 00:42:05.914
I need him to understand
what we've been through.

961
00:42:06.045 --> 00:42:07.612
Understand what?

962
00:42:08.700 --> 00:42:10.266
That I killed our boy?

963
00:42:10.397 --> 00:42:11.877
- Don't say that.
- No.

964
00:42:12.007 --> 00:42:14.183
It's true.

965
00:42:14.314 --> 00:42:15.750
I was the one driving.

966
00:42:15.924 --> 00:42:17.012
It was me.

967
00:42:17.143 --> 00:42:18.971
Nico should still be here.

968
00:42:19.145 --> 00:42:20.842
It was an accident.

969
00:42:21.930 --> 00:42:24.367
And I forgave him.

970
00:42:25.760 --> 00:42:28.197
- And he's forgiven me.
- Yeah.

971
00:42:28.328 --> 00:42:29.764
Doesn't that matter?

972
00:42:34.943 --> 00:42:36.597
Yes.

973
00:42:38.425 --> 00:42:40.862
Yes.

974
00:42:43.430 --> 00:42:46.564
Oh. fuck.

975
00:42:47.739 --> 00:42:49.175
No. please. Please!

976
00:42:49.349 --> 00:42:51.960
- No!
- FBI! Sean Fincher. drop your weapon!

977
00:43:04.625 --> 00:43:06.105
Oh. my God.

978
00:43:17.769 --> 00:43:19.553
Mom! Dad!

979
00:43:19.640 --> 00:43:21.860
Oh. God. Kima.
Thank God you're okay.

980
00:43:22.034 --> 00:43:24.993
Tough watching two sides of the
coin play out in front of you.

981
00:43:25.080 --> 00:43:26.952
If I'd thought of the
kids theory a half-step sooner.

982
00:43:27.082 --> 00:43:29.128
maybe Sean Fincher
doesn't have to die.

983
00:43:29.258 --> 00:43:32.044
And what if you'd have been
a half-step slower?

984
00:43:32.174 --> 00:43:34.002
Delores and Brenton are dead.

985
00:43:34.133 --> 00:43:37.484
That's right. Then we could've
lost two more innocent people.

986
00:43:37.615 --> 00:43:40.400
It's easy to see the glass
as half-empty right now.

987
00:43:40.574 --> 00:43:42.402
but experience has taught us...

988
00:43:42.532 --> 00:43:44.578
- Glass is half-full?
- No.

989
00:43:44.709 --> 00:43:46.319
The question you need
to ask yourself is

990
00:43:46.449 --> 00:43:48.364
did you do the job right?

991
00:43:48.495 --> 00:43:51.193
And if the answer is yes.

992
00:43:51.280 --> 00:43:53.021
fuck the glass.

993
00:44:01.073 --> 00:44:02.727
I just updated Prentiss.

994
00:44:02.857 --> 00:44:04.816
Uh. Laura Boyd's going to have
a security escort

995
00:44:04.946 --> 00:44:07.906
for the time being.
and I seriously doubt

996
00:44:08.036 --> 00:44:10.212
that Lance Kingston's
going to go anywhere near her

997
00:44:10.299 --> 00:44:11.474
anytime soon.

998
00:44:11.605 --> 00:44:14.173
Well. you were
pretty persuasive.

999
00:44:17.132 --> 00:44:18.960
Hey. Um...

1000
00:44:19.134 --> 00:44:20.745
I just...

1001
00:44:20.875 --> 00:44:23.791
- I just wanted to say thank you.
- For what?

1002
00:44:23.922 --> 00:44:25.314
The thing with Henry.

1003
00:44:25.445 --> 00:44:26.751
Did you guys talk?

1004
00:44:26.881 --> 00:44:28.927
No. Not yet.

1005
00:44:30.058 --> 00:44:31.843
But...

1006
00:44:31.930 --> 00:44:34.323
the more I think about it.
it just...

1007
00:44:34.454 --> 00:44:36.717
I don't know.
it just makes me happy

1008
00:44:36.848 --> 00:44:38.763
that he was able to talk to you.

1009
00:44:39.764 --> 00:44:41.766
Someone from our team.

1010
00:44:41.896 --> 00:44:45.204
Honestly. it's-it's been
good for me. too.

1011
00:44:45.291 --> 00:44:49.295
You know? To get to lend a hand
with the boys and...

1012
00:44:49.425 --> 00:44:51.427
just to be like an uncle
to them.

1013
00:44:51.514 --> 00:44:53.473
Whether you know it or not...

1014
00:44:54.474 --> 00:44:57.129
...you and Penelope...

1015
00:44:57.303 --> 00:45:00.915
you're... you're like
my extra eyes and ears.

1016
00:45:01.046 --> 00:45:03.570
You know. my village.

1017
00:45:03.701 --> 00:45:06.486
helps me care for the boys.

1018
00:45:06.660 --> 00:45:08.357
And. um...

1019
00:45:08.488 --> 00:45:10.664
look. as much
as I want him to have

1020
00:45:10.751 --> 00:45:12.361
that college dorm experience.

1021
00:45:12.448 --> 00:45:15.538
it's... it's his decision.

1022
00:45:16.670 --> 00:45:18.411
He'll tell you when he's ready.

1023
00:45:19.238 --> 00:45:20.935
Yeah. he will.

1024
00:45:22.458 --> 00:45:24.286
Ugh. kids.

1025
00:45:24.417 --> 00:45:27.594
They... they just zap your
worry button with no warning.

1026
00:45:29.117 --> 00:45:31.076
Well. I saw
some of that same worry

1027
00:45:31.206 --> 00:45:33.208
on Henry's face when he told me.

1028
00:45:33.339 --> 00:45:35.733
- Really?
- Yeah.

1029
00:45:35.820 --> 00:45:38.170
Wh-What... what is he
so worried about?

1030
00:45:38.300 --> 00:45:40.476
I don't know.

1031
00:45:40.607 --> 00:45:42.043
But I'm willing to bet

1032
00:45:42.130 --> 00:45:44.654
that he's ready to tell you.

1033
00:45:50.443 --> 00:45:51.618
Thanks.

1034
00:46:42.190 --> 00:46:43.191
Hey.

1035
00:46:46.804 --> 00:46:49.241
What? Is-is everything okay?

1036
00:46:49.415 --> 00:46:51.547
Oh. everything's fine.

1037
00:46:53.332 --> 00:46:55.116
Come on.

1038
00:46:55.247 --> 00:46:56.248
What time is it?

1039
00:46:56.335 --> 00:46:58.467
It's family time.

1040
00:47:03.646 --> 00:47:07.041
- Aren't you. like. super tired?
- Mm.

1041
00:47:08.477 --> 00:47:10.610
You know. a few years ago.
I would've said.

1042
00:47:10.784 --> 00:47:12.264
"No. I'm not tired."

1043
00:47:12.394 --> 00:47:14.440
Would've pushed through it. but

1044
00:47:14.570 --> 00:47:16.485
the truth is...

1045
00:47:16.616 --> 00:47:18.618
I'm exhausted.

1046
00:47:19.662 --> 00:47:21.577
What's with the ice cream?

1047
00:47:21.708 --> 00:47:23.928
Because. as tired as I am...

1048
00:47:25.233 --> 00:47:27.235
...nothing makes me happier than

1049
00:47:27.409 --> 00:47:31.196
sharing something sweet
with my firstborn.

1050
00:47:35.069 --> 00:47:36.375
Mom?

1051
00:47:38.856 --> 00:47:39.813
Yeah?

1052
00:47:39.987 --> 00:47:41.554
About college...

1053
00:47:41.684 --> 00:47:44.383
Luke told you. didn't he?

1054
00:47:46.907 --> 00:47:50.258
Well. you are turning into
quite the profiler. aren't you?

